00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.737
- [Voiceover] In recent
years the amount of C O two

00:00:02.737 --> 00:00:07.150
released by humans into
the planet has approached

00:00:07.150 --> 00:00:12.150
40 billion, 40 billion tons and if

00:00:12.407 --> 00:00:15.882
you wanted to break that
down based on people

00:00:15.882 --> 00:00:18.543
well we've recently crossed seven billion

00:00:18.543 --> 00:00:21.060
people on the planet so that's going to be

00:00:21.060 --> 00:00:26.052
approximately seven billion
people, seven billion people

00:00:26.772 --> 00:00:30.696
times the amount of tons per person

00:00:30.696 --> 00:00:32.180
and so if you work out the math,

00:00:32.180 --> 00:00:35.898
40 divided by seven is
going to be roughly 5.7

00:00:35.898 --> 00:00:40.898
5.7 tons per person, tons per person.

00:00:43.653 --> 00:00:45.548
And this might already seem like a lot,

00:00:45.548 --> 00:00:49.977
you can imagine 5.7 tons
of wood just being burned,

00:00:49.977 --> 00:00:52.781
actually it would have to be
more than 5.7 tons of wood

00:00:52.781 --> 00:00:55.361
because wood contains some water.

00:00:55.361 --> 00:00:58.146
But it's even more than that because,

00:00:58.146 --> 00:00:59.843
or at least for many of you all watching,

00:00:59.843 --> 00:01:01.754
it's going to be a lot more than that,

00:01:01.754 --> 00:01:03.887
because that's the
average of the developed

00:01:03.887 --> 00:01:06.204
and the developing world and it turns out

00:01:06.204 --> 00:01:09.028
that the average person
in the developed world,

00:01:09.028 --> 00:01:14.028
so developed, developed average,

00:01:14.208 --> 00:01:15.734
or if you're a wealthy person or a

00:01:15.734 --> 00:01:18.814
middle class person in
even the developing world,

00:01:18.814 --> 00:01:22.938
your average is going
to be closer to 20 tons,

00:01:22.938 --> 00:01:26.656
20 tons, per person, per year

00:01:26.656 --> 00:01:28.688
and in the developing world, or if you're

00:01:28.688 --> 00:01:30.537
not as wealthy of a
person or you're living

00:01:30.537 --> 00:01:32.223
in a rural place and
you're not using your car

00:01:32.223 --> 00:01:34.336
to get to where you need to get to

00:01:34.336 --> 00:01:36.124
or your house doesn't have electricity,

00:01:36.124 --> 00:01:41.049
so the poor, the poor, are using closer to

00:01:41.049 --> 00:01:46.049
one ton of C O two per person, per year.

00:01:47.014 --> 00:01:49.594
And so this already when
you even see this dynamic,

00:01:49.594 --> 00:01:51.624
it leads to something interesting.

00:01:51.624 --> 00:01:53.230
The number of people on the planet

00:01:53.230 --> 00:01:57.781
is only likely to increase
and we can see that.

00:01:57.781 --> 00:01:59.365
We have a little chart here from,

00:01:59.365 --> 00:02:02.170
based on data from the UN,
I know the numbers here

00:02:02.170 --> 00:02:03.896
are a little bit small, it starts in 1800

