00:09:03.460 --> 00:09:07.585
per service by 80% or even 90%

00:09:07.585 --> 00:09:10.836
you still have many
tens of billions of tons

00:09:10.836 --> 00:09:13.660
of C O two being released every year.

00:09:13.660 --> 00:09:15.935
So the only way we're going
to be able to get that,

00:09:15.935 --> 00:09:18.818
to get this thing down to zero,

00:09:18.818 --> 00:09:22.831
is if, is if C, right over here,

00:09:22.831 --> 00:09:25.900
the C O two released per unit of energy

00:09:25.900 --> 00:09:30.900
goes to zero, it needs, so
this needs to go to zero.

00:09:33.433 --> 00:09:36.987
Which is a fairly bold
thing to say because

00:09:36.987 --> 00:09:38.755
we're nowhere close to that right now

00:09:38.755 --> 00:09:40.766
but if we're serious about this,

00:09:40.766 --> 00:09:43.001
it's possible that humanity can get there.

00:09:43.001 --> 00:09:46.658
There are energy sources
that are, that don't

00:09:46.658 --> 00:09:50.640
release C O two or get pretty
close to being at zero.

00:09:50.640 --> 00:09:52.245
And just to be clear,
even if you're driving

00:09:52.245 --> 00:09:54.317
an electric car, you have to think about

00:09:54.317 --> 00:09:56.004
where does that electricity come from?

00:09:56.004 --> 00:09:58.584
If that electricity
was generated using say

00:09:58.584 --> 00:10:01.225
something like coal, well
that's going to release C O two

00:10:01.225 --> 00:10:04.821
or if it was generated using natural gas,

00:10:04.821 --> 00:10:08.438
that is going to release
carbon into the atmosphere.

00:10:08.438 --> 00:10:10.744
And so you need to think about,

00:10:10.744 --> 00:10:11.499
even if you are using something

00:10:11.499 --> 00:10:13.978
like an electric motor, how is that

00:10:13.978 --> 00:10:16.477
electricity actually produced?

00:10:16.477 --> 00:10:18.509
And you have energy sources, like nuclear,

00:10:18.509 --> 00:10:19.951
nuclear has it's own set of issues

00:10:19.951 --> 00:10:21.719
that we think about, like safety

00:10:21.719 --> 00:10:23.202
and what you do with the waste

00:10:23.202 --> 00:10:24.279
but people are working on things

00:10:24.279 --> 00:10:26.371
like clean burning nuclear
that are much safer

00:10:26.371 --> 00:10:30.536
and generate a very small
fraction of the waste.

00:10:30.536 --> 00:10:33.178
You have all your other
renewable souces of energy

00:10:33.178 --> 00:10:35.087
but this is a big challenge for humanity.

00:10:35.087 --> 00:10:37.668
If we want this thing
on the left to be zero,

00:10:37.668 --> 00:10:41.754
if we wanna slow, or if we wanna

